title: Moore's RPG Template
description: High Fantasy Single Player RPG Template
longDescription:
(Free for the Month of August 2024) Welcome to Moore’s RPG Template version 2.12.1 released August 21st 2024 (also known as the MRPGT), a “complete project”, from Moore Game Dev. It is a First and Third Person, Single Player, High Fantasy, RPG Core Framework. It includes user interfaces, blueprints, props, animations, a sample character and other content that can be used as the basis for a “medieval high fantasy RPG”. The intention of this kit is to provide you with most of the core systems that would permit you to create a single player RPG similar in functionality and gameplay to Skyrim.

Features

  1. Book reading system
  2. Lockpicking system
  3. Civilian clothing
  4. Chainmail armour
  5. Plate armour
  6. Sample knight character
  7. Loot tables
  8. Map, minimap and compass system
  9. Fast travel system
  10. Sample landscape
  11. Medieval Buildings Volume 1 included
  12. Non-humanoid combat system
  13. Follower system
  14. Dialogue system
  15. Mount system
  16. Character management system
  17. Item management system
  18. Spell management and spell casting system
  19. Perk system
  20. Skill Levelling system
  21. Level Up system
  22. Ingredient Harvesting system
  23. Favourite system
  24. Trading system
  25. Quest system
  26. Crafting system
  27. Enchanting system
  28. Health, stamina and power bars
  29. Combat system with multiple weapon types and combo attacks
  30. NPC Combat AI
  31. Stealth system
  32. Save game system
  33. Gamepad controls
  34. Main menu and options system
  35. Sample equipment, spells, perks, animations and more
  36. Source Blender, Maya and Substance Painter files included


Overview video: https://youtu.be/6m6pvyYKe7A
technicalDetails:
Asset Statistics

The package includes Epic Games demo assets. The number of non-demo assets are as follows:

  • Animation Sequences: 291
  • Animation Montages: 51
  • Animation Blueprints: 6
  • Animation Blendspaces: 17
  • Animation Offsets: 3
  • Animation Notify States: 6
  • AI Behaviour Trees: 3
  • AI Blueprints: 105
  • Widget Blueprints: 55
  • Other Blueprints: 111
  • Materials: 140
  • Material Instances: 490
  • Textures: 1900
  • Sound waves: 119
  • Niagara Systems: 34
  • Static Meshes: 731
  • Skeletal Meshes: 64
  • Levels: 2

Other information

  • Rigged to Epic skeleton: Yes (man, clothing and armour yes, horse no, bow no)
  • Epic skeleton version: UE5
  • Supported Dev & Target Platforms: Windows
  • User Guide: https://bit.ly/3Iy7mFj
  • Preconfigured Input: Keyboard, Mouse, Gamepad
  • Network Replicated: No (if any competent C++ dev wants to offer their programming services to add this feature for money please contact me).
  • Tech Support: Use the Discord Server, #support channel, below.
  • Discord Server: https://discord.gg/gqVSZ2STqP
  • Playable Demo of v2.12 : https://bit.ly/45V8tv5 (works fine on my RTX3060 Ryzen3600 32GB RAM computer)
  • Roadmap: https://bit.ly/3AH1jeS
